### 4. CSS (Web Styling)
```css
/* Styling for the main container */
.container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    min-height: 100vh;
    background-color: #f0f2f5;
    font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
}

/* Button hover effect */
button {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    font-size: 16px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background-color 0.3s ease, transform 0.1s;
}

button:hover {
    background-color: #007bff;
    color: white;
}

button:active {
    transform: scale(0.95);
}
```

### 5. C++ (Systems Programming)
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>

int main() {
    std::vector<int> numbers = {42, 7, 19, 1, 55, 12};

    std::cout << "Original vector: ";
    for (int n : numbers) std::cout << n << " ";
    std::cout << std::endl;

    // Sort the vector
    std::sort(numbers.begin(), numbers.end());

    std::cout << "Sorted vector:   ";
    for (int n : numbers) std::cout << n << " ";
    std::cout << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

**What to check in your UI:**
1.  **Syntax Highlighting:** Do different parts of the code (keywords, strings, comments, numbers) have different colors?
2.  **Indentation:** Is the hierarchical structure of the code preserved?
3.  **Font:** Does it use a monospaced font (like Courier, Consolas, or Fira Code)?
4.  **Overflow:** If a line of code is very long, does it wrap to the next line or provide a horizontal scrollbar?
